HEADWORD: Autopathic
<hw>Au`to*path"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Auto-</er>, and <er>Pathic</er>, <pos>a.</pos>]</ety>
<fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>Dependent upon, or due or relating to, the
structure and characteristics of the diseased organism; endopathic;
<as>as, an <ex>autopathic</ex> disease; an <ex>autopathic</ex> theory of
diseases</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
